1️⃣ failure is part of the GAME. i now expect 99 no’s and (maybe) 1 yes.

Cinnamon Roll GB Monkey Bread 🥵 
Ingredients:
- ½ cup granulated sugar
- 1 teaspoon ground cinnamon
- 2 cans @pillsbury biscuits
- 1 cup packed brown sugar
- ¾ cup butter, melted
- ½ cup cinnamon roll granola butter

Instructions:
1️⃣ Heat oven to 325°F. Lightly grease 12-cup fluted tube cake pan. 
2️⃣ In large plastic food-storage bag, mix granulated sugar and cinnamon. Separate dough into a total of 16 biscuits; cut each into quarters. Shake in bag to coat. Arrange in pan. Mix brown sugar, granola butter and butter; pour over biscuit pieces.
3️⃣ Bake 47 to 52 minutes or until golden brown and no longer doughy in center. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Turn upside down onto serving plate; pull apart to serve. Faceplant 😈

COOKING WITH ALI: red velvet whoopie pies 🥵🥵 recipe ⬇️

Red Velvet Whoopie Pies‼️
Ingredients:
1 box red velvet cake mix
1/2 cup water
1/2 cup vegetable oil
3 large eggs
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 can cream cheese frosting
2 tablespoons @oat.haus red velvet granola butter

Instructions:
1️⃣ Preheat your oven to 350 degrees. Line two or three cookie trays with parchment and set aside.
2️⃣ Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Whisk together until the batter is smooth.
3️⃣ Drop by heaping tablespoon full onto your prepared sheets leaving at least a 2 inch space between each cookie.
4️⃣ Bake 10-12 minutes. Allow to cool completely.
5️⃣ While cookies are cooling, fold granola butter into cream cheese frosting.
6️⃣ Spread 1-2 tablespoons of frosting between two cookies. Continue with remaining cookies.

EGG FREEZING ✅ my top tips if you’re considering freezing your eggs:

🥚learn from my mistakes and do it during a slower time of year, work-wise. you will feel unmotivated and brain foggy from the hormones

🥚if you’re terrified of needles, SAME — but I promise you can do it! the needle is as thin as a strand of hair, teeny tiny! you don’t feel it, it’s more of a mental hurdle. there are also companies that can come to your house and inject you, but it’s really empowering to do it yourself 🦸🏼‍♀️

🥚buy a heating pad & electrolytes for post-retrieval — game changers!

🥚document your journey 🎥!! even if you share with no one, it’s really cool to look back on & see how far you’ve come

🥚if you live alone, facetime a friend to do your first injection with you 💖

🥚you’ll do injections for ~10 days. make ZERO social plans the last few days — you will feel super uncomfortably bloated and exhausted 😴 

🥚sleep as much as you can and nourish your body however feels good to you. it’s going through a lot!!!

lmk your questions below and i’ll do my best to help 🥹🙏🏼

whew — this post has been a long time coming (buckle up!)

when I started this account six years ago, social media was a very different place. for me it was a personal diary, a place to express my thoughts and feelings with whoever would take the time to listen

over time, the app changed and evolved — video replaced photos, and tiktok dances replaced heartfelt captions

the algorithm rewards fluffy, cookie cutter content — and in complete honesty, i‘ve been struggling with it

i tried for a while.. but found myself feeling like an imposter. because when creative inspiration strikes, I like to share right then and there. from the heart. truly in the moment

video and reels don’t really allow for that — you need to edit, record a voice over.. don’t even get me started on picking a trending song! 😅

and so in many ways, i lost my way. fell victim to creating content in hopes of going viral. feeling lost and uninspired. losing sight of why I created this account in the first place — to share the ups and downs of my human experience 

but there’s still this rich, creative supernova of thoughts and words inside of me that needs to be shared. and instead of appeasing the instagram algorithm gods, i’m gonna do it my way, baby 🤸🏼‍♀️ 

back to basics. back to the old instagram. and if it flops, oh well — this one’s for me 😗✌🏼

really blown away by the response to my post last night 🥹💖💫 guess i’m not the only one who’s been feeling this way!!!

I woke up feeling like every cell in my body was doing cartwheels 🤸🏼‍♀️🌼 

I feel alive, energized, electric!!!⚡️like my passion for creating on this app is coming back 🥹💖

reading through your comments, I realized it’s not about posts, videos, or reels. it’s about taking our power back and posting whatever-the-hell-you-wanna-post 😗✌🏼

so whether that’s a video, a drawing, a quote… the form doesn’t matter. what matters is we’re creating something that’s uniquely and beautifully ourselves — not to please some algorithm lottery 🎰

cheers to showing up as authentically US, even if it’s not trendy or cool or viral 🪐🥂

something i’m currently struggling with? having fun 🫠🫠🫠

i’m *great* at being an adult. phenomenal. in fact, i’ve been an adult since i was 5 years old 

when i was in middle school, i used to wake up at 6am to make lunches for everyone in my family. no one asked me to do this — i just did it 😆 (nerd alert!)

excelling at adulting has served me in a lot of ways: i got into a great college, i started my own business.. but it’s also a fast-track to burnout — and not what life is all about!!!

like you, i’m busy as helllll — so “planning fun” (especially during the work week) can feel overwhelming

what’s helped me? incorporating little moments of fun in my everyday — here’s what i did to fill my fun bucket today:

✅ put on a colorful outfit 
✅ walk with a friend
✅ try out a new coffee shop
✅ eat a pastry for breakfast

what are you doing for fun today? 🕺🏻🪩⭐️

I’m a nervous flyer. 

and how could I not be? a metal tube, hurdling 500mph, 30,000 feet above the earth?! make it make sense! 

but the more I thought about it, I realized — its not the heights, or enclosed spaces that scare me. it’s the loss of control. 

so really, i’m a nervous flyer — AND a control freak 😆 

I know being in control is one of the biggest illusions we tell ourselves — take the pandemic, for example. a perfect reminder that yeah… we don’t have much control over what happens. 

but the one thing we do have control over? ourselves. how we respond. amazing!!!

so as i’m sitting here, sweaty as hell, in this metal tube… I can lean into surrendering 

lean into the anxiety, without fighting it

lean into excitement of seeing my friends and family

and lastly: lean into knowing that this flight is completely out of my control — because it’s in the hands of people who fly planes much better than I do 🫠🫠🫠

it’s a funny feeling; knowing i’m living 3,000 miles away from a place that makes me the happiest 

2 years ago, we packed up everything we had and moved to philly, a city I had only visited once before 

i’ve done everything you’re supposed to do to make a place feel like home:

I made friends
I tried new restaurants 
I went to sporting events 
I found “my coffee shop”
I embraced the seasons 

and 2 years later… it still doesn’t feel like home

but i’m realizing — maybe not everywhere I live has to feel like home??

maybe home is home; and other cities serve different purposes

knowing philly is the right move for the business, even though my heart is elsewhere

and that’s okay 🥲🏡

this weekend, I spent time with friends I had drifted apart from

life happened, I told myself 
we moved away, I told myself
things got busy, I told myself

when in reality — the reason we drifted apart is because I overthink reasons to not call them

“it’s been too long”
“they’ll think it’s weird if I reach out randomly”
“they’re busy”
“i’m busy”

when we talked about it this weekend — they told me they were thinking the same thing!!! 

we’re all desperate for connection yet terrified of connection 🥲

from now on, i’m going to call friends when I think of them 

it’s ok if they don’t answer 
it’s ok if i’m nervous 
it’s ok if I don’t know what to say

life is too short to lose touch with incredible people 🥹💖

my first cheesecake 🥹🫶🏻 this recipe is a winner!!! from @bonappetitmag — I halved the recipe & used GF flour in place of regular. I’m gonna try 10 min less baking next time, to see if it’s creamier and less firm 🤸🏼‍♀️🤸🏼‍♀️🤸🏼‍♀️

1 lb. cream cheese, room temperature
3/4 cup sugar
3 large eggs
1 cup heavy cream
1/2 tsp. kosher salt

I love to travel, but I don’t love the flying part, especially TURBULENCE 🫠🫠🫠

but learning this ONE IDEA made something click in my brain 🧠 — and now I have way less anxiety when i’m on a plane: 

it’s called THE JELLO THEORY, and I saw it from @anna_paull on tiktok ‼️ 

at very high speeds, the air becomes very thick (like jello!) and the plane is in the middle of it. there’s pressure on all sides — so the plane is suspended in air (like jello!) and it won’t drop out of the sky. 

sometimes the plane shakes and quivers (like jello!) but it’s similar to hitting a pothole in the road — annoying, but nothing life threatening 💘

have you heard of this?!
